Microlearning History App
Project Overview
This app is designed to provide bite-sized historical lessons in a microlearning format, inspired by apps like Duolingo and news aggregators. The goal is to make history learning more accessible, engaging, and tailored to user preferences.

Features
Scrollable Feed: Displays bite-sized historical lessons.

Personalized Recommendations: An algorithm suggests content based on user interests.

Database-Driven Content: Lessons are stored in a database and dynamically loaded into the app.

Tech Stack
Frontend: TypeScript, HTML, CSS

Backend: Node.js (planned for database interactions)

Database: MongoDB (or similar, for storing content)

UI/UX Design: Custom-designed to enhance user experience.

Current Progress
- Basic app layout and design are in place.

- Working on scrollable feed functionality.

- Preparing to populate the database with accurate, engaging historical lessons.

- Developing an algorithm for personalized content recommendations.
Feedback

If you have ideas, suggestions, or want to contribute to the project, feel free to reach out or open an issue on GitHub.
